<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?><?Xpress productLine="ncc-clause" ?><clause id="_ed91f268-a0a2-430e-81ac-a641f8c093e3" outputclass="ncc-clause"><meta><facet building="Class 2"/><facet building="Class 3"/><facet building="Class 4"/><facet building="Class 5"/><facet building="Class 6"/><facet building="Class 7a"/><facet building="Class 7b"/><facet building="Class 8"/><facet building="Class 9a"/><facet building="Class 9b"/><facet building="Class 9c"/><facet building="Class 10b"/><facet building="Class 10c"/><facet climate="Climate zone 8"/></meta><sptc>5.5.3</sptc><title id="_a0a8d24b-cca8-40da-83c9-c46d10e1bb00">Isolated piers supporting tiled roofs</title><archive-num>2019: 3.3.6.3</archive-num><subclause id="_fa4c6aa3-32f1-47d0-a139-4da2d3aa2409" outputclass="subclause"><title id="_06b562ab-e1e4-4755-b6b7-0cc5a2dc18b7">SubClause</title><num>1</num><p>Isolated piers supporting tiled roofs must have—</p><ol outputclass="alpha"><li id="_47a995a5-a93f-4690-93d2-71eb3b0bd8db">a built-in 30 x 0.8 mm galvanised steel strap fixed to the roof structure that extends the full height of the pier; and</li><li id="_044f0839-b530-4c69-9ffd-ff4fa1d758bc">a 4.6 grade M12 galvanised steel rod which is cast into the footing when poured and looped and fixed around the galvanised steel strap <xref xmlns:inv="urn:xpressauthor:xpressdocument" format="dita" href="/tmp/QppServer/Publishing/601d5817-38d4-46f4-a9ae-3e54027c73d5/1432_4.0.0.xml#_af6fde9f-147d-4782-8b85-42044e80fd42" id="_04ec55c3-b0aa-4401-81a3-bef4e5c28149" inv:access="external" scope="local" type="abcb-glossentry">required</xref> by (a).</li></ol></subclause></clause>